In the difficult hour of the impending omicron wave, the city government took unprecedented measures and redesigned district clinics into multifunctional centers. Doctors locked themselves in their offices, nurses were given the first line of defense. The task of citizens was to receive a QR code. The set of obstacles is standard, signing up for public services, then a live queue, then screams from the office: Wait, we have another job, and then lunch. Then collecting information, a quest in telegram No. still occupied. For this, two packs of free paracetamol are required. For all one week of sick leave. Everyone became cheerful, lean, there was no time to get sick. And so they won.